Turkey calls out U.S. diplomat over spying allegations
The Turkish Foreign Ministry has summoned the highest-ranking American diplomat in the country for clarification in connection with a report on American and British espionage in Turkey.
Deputy Prime Minister Bulent said the U.S. commissioner and Turkish officials discussed the announcement on Monday.
The German magazine Der Spiegel and the online magazine The Intercept that documents provided by former U.S. National Security Agency analyst Edward Snowden show that Turkey was a priority intelligence target for U.S. and British intelligence services.
