Two other local police officers have been arrested by the Spanish National Guard on corruption charges and will be questioned by a judge along with Navarro.
The Spanish daily ABC that dissatisfied nightclub owners say protectionism from the authorities is seriously affecting their business.
“It’s not about making money anymore, it’s about surviving,” one of the businessmen told the court.
We must not jeopardize our sources of existence.
We have nothing to lose.
Magaluf came to the headlines of the international press this summer after a popular YouTube video showing an 18-year-old British vacationer killing 24 men while running in bars.
The authorities of the island have since tried to stop the hooliganism in the drunken state among the holidaymakers of Magaluf, minimizing the number of scandalously famous alcoholic runs in bars.
