Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd NCHL.O, the world’s third-largest cruise operator, is in the final phase of negotiations to acquire the similar company Prestige Cruises International Inc. for approximately $3 billion, according to people familiar with the situation.
The deal would give Norwegian Cruise, a $6.8 billion market-value company, access to luxury cruise ships and well-off Prestige Cruises customers as it competes with larger rivals Royal Caribbean Cruises Ltd (RCL.N) and Carnival Corp (CCL.N).
