Based in Miami, Norwegian Cruise operates 13 cruise ships on routes covering North America, the Mediterranean, the Baltic Sea, Central America and the Caribbean.
Her revenue was $2.57 billion in 2013, 13 percent more than in 2012.
Prestige Cruises, also based in Miami, operates under the brands Oceania and Regent, which together own eight cruise ships that travel to Scandinavia, Russia, the Mediterranean, North America, Asia, Africa and South America.
She revenue of $1.2 billion in 2013, 6 percent higher than a year earlier.
The $29 billion cruise industry is expected to have a positive impact on middle-class growth in emerging economies such as China and India in the coming years.
