Prestige Cruises was registered with U.S. regulators for primary public placement in January 2014.
Apollo became the company’s main shareholder after a $850 million deal in 2007.
Norwegian Cruise was created as it exists today in 2000 as a result of a merger with a cruise operator owned by Genting Bhd (GENT.KL), an entertainment and casino conglomerate controlled by Malaysian billionaire Lim Kok Tea.
Apollo invested $1 billion in Norwegian Cruise in 2008.
Norwegian Cruise became a public company in January 2013.
Genting owned 28 percent, Apollo owned 20 percent, and private investment firm TPG Capital LP owned 8 percent of the company, according to the report.
Carnival, Royal Caribbean Cruises and Norwegian Cruise together account for 82 percent of the cruise passenger traffic in North America, according to registration documents at the first public placement of Prestige Cruises shares.
